cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the problem of data dissemination in mobile social networks, which involves communication and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a game-theoretic approach to solve the joint head selection and airtime allocation problem, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization problems and algorithms for the proposed scheme, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents numerical results to evaluate the performance of the proposed scheme, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
